HEADWORD: Quinquefid
<hw>Quin"que*fid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Quique-</ets> + the root of L. <ets>findere</ets> to cleave:
cf. F. <ets>quinqu⟦eacute⟧fide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Sharply cut about halfway to the middle or base into five segments;
<as>as, a <ex>quinquefid</ex> leaf or corolla</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
